@page "/integrations"
<PageTitle>Integrations - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="integrations">Integrations</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Saascade components integrate with the standard Blazor ecosystem.
                They work in Blazor WebAssembly, Blazor Server, and .NET MAUI Blazor Hybrid
                projects without additional configuration.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Any library or tool that works with standard Blazor components works with
                Saascade components. The library does not introduce custom rendering pipelines,
                non-standard lifecycle methods, or proprietary JavaScript dependencies.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="asset-references">Asset References</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The DesignSystemStylesheetReferences and DesignSystemJavaScriptReferences
                components inject the stylesheet and script links required by the active
                design system into the page.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Place DesignSystemStylesheetReferences in the head of your index.html or
                App.razor layout. Place DesignSystemJavaScriptReferences before the closing
                body tag. The components call GetStylesheetReferences and GetJavaScriptReferences
                on the registered IDesignSystem and render the appropriate link and script tags.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="integrations-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Integration</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Integration</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Bootstrap 5 integration requires no JavaScript interop beyond what Bootstrap
                itself provides. The VanillaBootstrap5 design system returns Bootstrap's CDN
                stylesheet URL from GetStylesheetReferences and Bootstrap's bundle script URL
                from GetJavaScriptReferences. Bootstrap interactive components such as modals
                and dropdowns work through standard Bootstrap JavaScript after the bundle loads.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="integrations-daisyui">DaisyUI Integration</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Integration</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                DaisyUI integration is CSS-only — DaisyUI components are driven by CSS rather
                than JavaScript. The DaisyUI design system returns the Tailwind plus DaisyUI CDN
                stylesheet from GetStylesheetReferences and returns no JavaScript references.
                Interactive DaisyUI patterns such as dropdowns and modals use CSS-only mechanisms
                and work without any JavaScript initialization.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="integrations-basecoat">Basecoat Integration</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Integration</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Basecoat integration is also CSS-only, built on Tailwind utility classes.
                The Basecoat design system returns the Tailwind plus Basecoat CDN stylesheet
                from GetStylesheetReferences and no JavaScript references. Because Basecoat
                uses pure utility classes without component-level JavaScript, it integrates
                cleanly with Blazor's server-side rendering and prerendering pipelines.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("integrations", "Integrations"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("asset-references", "Asset References", 2),
    new TocItem("integrations-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2),
    new TocItem("integrations-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2),
    new TocItem("integrations-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2)
])" />

</div>
